lized": false, "mention": "CYP2E1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9778091311454773, "span": {"begin": 456, "end": 462}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9964035749435425, "span": {"begin": 526, "end": 531}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1571"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CYP2E1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9738983511924744, "span": {"begin": 560, "end": 566}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1571"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CYP2E1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9843197464942932, "span": {"begin": 616, "end": 622}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1571"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CYP2E1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9711726903915405, "span": {"begin": 730, "end": 736}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000431"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ethanol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9938623905181885, "span": {"begin": 763, "end": 770}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1571"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CYP2E1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9630461931228638, "span": {"begin": 794, "end": 800}}], "text": "CYP2E1 is an enzyme which is part of the cytochrome P450 family. It participates in the metabolism of endogenous, small and hydrophobic compounds using an oxidation reaction. CYP2E1 requires phospholipids, NADPH, and NADPH-cytochrome P450 reductase as a cofactor for catalytic activity in vitro. The level of CYP2E1 in the brain of a rat is significantly low, only 25% of what is found in rat liver cells. Inside a brain cell of a rat the highest level of CYP2E1 is found in the mitochondria and the endoplasmic reticulum. In human brain samples expression of CYP2E1 was found in the amygdala and prefrontal cortex. CYP2E1 is also known to activate toxic related compounds (see stressors). Another important consideration is that CYP2E1 is part of the microsomal ethanol oxidizing system. When CYP2E1 is stimulated at constant rate the concentration of the enzyme in the cell will rise.&nbsp;(Garci&aacute;-Su&aacute;stegui, W. A. et al.,&nbsp;2017;&nbsp;Howard, L. A.&nbsp;et al., 2003;&nbsp;Neafsey, P. et al.,&nbsp;2009;&nbsp;Toselli, F. et al,&nbsp;2015;&nbsp;Zimatkin, S. M.&nbsp;et al,&nbsp;2006)", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:43:11 +0000 2026"}